SELECT followee follower, COUNT(DISTINCT follower) num FROM follow WHERE followee IN (SELECT follower FROM follow) GROUP BY 1
SELECT f1.follower, COUNT(DISTINCT f2.follower) as num FROM follow f1 INNER JOIN follow f2 ON f1.follower=f2.followee GROUP BY f1.follower ORDER BY f1.follower

with cte as ( select distinct follower as follower from follow ) select cte.follower, count(distinct f.follower) as num from cte left join follow f on cte.follower = f.followee group by cte.follower having num >= 1
select followee as follower, count(distinct follower) as num from follow where followee in (select follower from follow) group by 1 order by 1
SELECT followee AS follower, COUNT(DISTINCT follower) AS num FROM follow WHERE followee IN (SELECT follower FROM follow) GROUP BY followee
select f1.follower as follower, count(distinct f2.follower) as num from Follow f1 left join Follow f2 on f1.follower = f2.followee where f2.followee is not null group by f1.follower
Select f1.follower, count(distinct f2.follower) as num from follow f1 inner join follow f2 on f1.follower = f2.followee Group by f1.follower
select a.follower, count(distinct b.follower) as num from follow a left join follow b on a.follower = b.followee group by a.follower having count(distinct b.follower) > 0
SELECT t1.follower,Count(distinct(t2.follower)) AS num FROM FOLLOW T1 LEFT JOIN FOLLOW T2 ON T1.FOLLOWER = T2.FOLLOWEE WHERE t2.follower is not null GROUP BY T1.FOLLOWER order by t1.follower
select f1.follower,count(distinct f2.follower) num from follow f1 left join follow f2 on f1.follower= f2.followee where f2.followee is not null group by f1.follower
